                            <comment id="14662194" author="vrodionov" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2015 18:15:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ConnectionCache was introduced in 0.98.4/0.99 and all HBase active versions are affected by this bug. In a few words, If cached connection stays idle for more than connection idle timeout (10 min) it is closed, but stays in a cache, all table instances in Thrift servers related to this connection becomes invalid, all Thrift requests from a particular user start failing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
